article.description: Dedrick Basile scored a career-high 30 points, Damiyne Durham added 24 -- both going 6 of 12 from 3-point range -- and Cal State Bakersfield rolled to a 105-78 win over Division II Bethesda on Th
article.headline: Basile has 30, Durham 24 as Bakersfield tops Bethesda 105-78
article.linkText: Basile has 30, Durham 24 as Bakersfield tops Bethesda 105-78
article.story: BAKERSFIELD, Calif. -- Dedrick Basile scored a career-high 30 points, Damiyne Durham added 24 -- both going 6 of 12 from 3-point range -- and Cal State Bakersfield rolled to a 105-78 win over Division II Bethesda on Thursday. Basile and Durham both had five 3s, combining for 40 points in the first half when the Roadrunners (8-4) shot 64 percent (21 of 33) to open a 60-36 lead. Fallou Ndoye added 12 points and nine rebounds for the Roadrunners, who had a 50-25 advantage on the boards, 20-7 on the offensive end. Basile and Brent Wrapp had six assists as Bakersfield field ended up with 27 helpers on 33 baskets. Jarrell Tate had 20 points and nine assists for Bethesda, which counted the game as an exhibition, and Buddha Boyd had 16 points. The pair combined for seven 3s as the Flames went 17 of 33 behind the arc.
